{
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "$schema": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/sarif/sarif/v2.1.0/errata01/os/schemas/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "grype",
          "version": "0.114.0",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-55200-libssh2-1t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-55200 critical vulnerability for libssh2-1t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "libssh2 through 1.11.1, fixed in commit 7acf3df contains an out-of-bounds write vulnerability in ssh2_transport_read() that fails to enforce upper bounds on packet_length field. Remote attackers can send crafted SSH packets with excessively large packet_length values to corrupt heap memory and achieve remote code execution."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-55200",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-55200\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: libssh2-1t64\nVersion: 1.11.1-3\nFix Version: 1.11.1-4\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-55200](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-55200)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-55200**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | libssh2-1t64  | 1.11.1-3  | 1.11.1-4  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-55200](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-55200)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libssh2-1t64@1.11.1-3?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=libssh2"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.2"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42496-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42496 critical vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Archive::Tar versions before 3.08 for Perl extract symlinks with attacker controlled targets outside the extraction directory.  _make_special_file() passes the tar header's linkname to symlink() without validating it against absolute paths or .. segments. The secure-extract mode check that guards regular file extraction does not cover the symlink target.  A subsequent open through the extracted name reads or writes the attacker chosen path."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-42496\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-8\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-42496](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-42496**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-8  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-42496](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-8?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.1"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-5450-libc-bin",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-5450 critical vulnerability for libc-bin package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Calling the scanf family of functions with a %mc (malloc'd character match) in the GNU C Library version 2.7 to version 2.43 with a format width specifier with an explicit width greater than 1024 could result in a one byte heap buffer overflow."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: libc-bin\nVersion: 2.42-16\nFix Version: 2.42-17\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-5450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | libc-bin  | 2.42-16  | 2.42-17  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-5450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libc-bin@2.42-16?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=glibc"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-5450-libc-gconv-modules-extra",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-5450 critical vulnerability for libc-gconv-modules-extra package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Calling the scanf family of functions with a %mc (malloc'd character match) in the GNU C Library version 2.7 to version 2.43 with a format width specifier with an explicit width greater than 1024 could result in a one byte heap buffer overflow."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: libc-gconv-modules-extra\nVersion: 2.42-16\nFix Version: 2.42-17\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-5450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | libc-gconv-modules-extra  | 2.42-16  | 2.42-17  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-5450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libc-gconv-modules-extra@2.42-16?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=glibc"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-5450-libc6",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-5450 critical vulnerability for libc6 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Calling the scanf family of functions with a %mc (malloc'd character match) in the GNU C Library version 2.7 to version 2.43 with a format width specifier with an explicit width greater than 1024 could result in a one byte heap buffer overflow."
              },
