              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: libc6\nVersion: 2.42-16\nFix Version: 2.42-17\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-5450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-5450**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | libc6  | 2.42-16  | 2.42-17  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-5450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libc6@2.42-16?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=glibc"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.8"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-12087-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-12087 critical vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Socket versions before 2.041 for Perl have an out-of-bounds heap read.  In Socket.xs, pack_ip_mreq_source() checks the length of its source argument before the argument is read, so the check tests the byte length carried over from the preceding multiaddr argument instead. Both addresses occupy a 4-byte field, so a valid multiaddr lets a source of any length pass the check, and the source is then copied into the 4-byte imr_sourceaddr field with a fixed-size copy. A source shorter than 4 bytes is not rejected, and the copy reads up to 3 bytes past the end of its buffer.  Calling pack_ip_mreq_source() with a source value shorter than 4 bytes copies adjacent heap memory into the returned packed structure."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-12087",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-12087\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-8\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-12087](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-12087)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-12087**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-8  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-12087](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-12087)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-8?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.1"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2017-17740-libldap2",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2017-17740 low vulnerability for libldap2 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "contrib/slapd-modules/nops/nops.c in OpenLDAP through 2.4.45, when both the nops module and the memberof overlay are enabled, attempts to free a buffer that was allocated on the stack, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (slapd crash) via a member MODDN operation."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-17740",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2017-17740\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libldap2\nVersion: 2.6.10+dfsg-1+b2\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2017-17740](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-17740)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2017-17740**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | libldap2  | 2.6.10+dfsg-1+b2  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2017-17740](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-17740)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libldap2@2.6.10%2Bdfsg-1%2Bb2?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=openldap%402.6.10%2Bdfsg-1"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-9538-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-9538 high vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Archive::Tar versions before 3.10 for Perl allow memory exhaustion via attacker controlled entry size field in tar header.  _read_tar() reads each entry's payload with $handle-\u003eread($$data, $block), where $block is derived from the entry's 12-byte size field in the tar header with no upper bound on that value.  A crafted header declaring a multi-gigabyte size causes Perl to allocate a scalar of that size."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-9538",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-9538\nSeverity: high\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-8\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-9538](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-9538)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-9538**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-8  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-9538](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-9538)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-8?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42497-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42497 high vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Archive::Tar versions before 3.08 for Perl extract hardlinks to attacker controlled paths outside the extraction directory.  _make_special_file() passes the tar header's linkname to link() without validating it against absolute paths or .. segments, creating a hardlink that shares the victim file's inode.  A subsequent write through the extracted name modifies the victim file, and the post-extraction chmod, chown, and utime block in _extract_file() (guarded only against symlinks via -l) applies the tar header's mode, owner, and timestamps to the shared inode during extraction alone."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-42497\nSeverity: high\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-8\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-42497](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-42497**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-8  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-42497](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-8?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-55199-libssh2-1t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-55199 high vulnerability for libssh2-1t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "libssh2 through 1.11.1, fixed in commit 1762685, contains a pre-authentication denial of service vulnerability in the SSH_MSG_EXT_INFO handler in src/packet.c that allows a malicious SSH server to cause a client CPU exhaustion loop by sending a crafted extension count value. A malicious server can set nr_extensions to 0xFFFFFFFF during key exchange, causing the client to spin in a tight CPU loop for over 60 seconds because return values from _libssh2_get_string() are unchecked and the session timeout does not apply to CPU-bound loops."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-55199",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-55199\nSeverity: high\nPackage: libssh2-1t64\nVersion: 1.11.1-3\nFix Version: 1.11.1-4\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-55199](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-55199)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-55199**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | libssh2-1t64  | 1.11.1-3  | 1.11.1-4  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-55199](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-55199)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libssh2-1t64@1.11.1-3?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=libssh2"
                ],
                "security-severity": "8.2"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2018-20796-libc-bin",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2018-20796 low vulnerability for libc-bin package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "In the GNU C Library (aka glibc or libc6) through 2.29, check_dst_limits_calc_pos_1 in posix/regexec.c has Uncontrolled Recursion, as demonstrated by '(\\227|)(\\\\1\\\\1|t1|\\\\\\2537)+' in grep."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2018-20796",
