            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-11850-libgssapi-krb5-2",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-11850 low vulnerability for libgssapi-krb5-2 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An integer underflow vulnerability was found in MIT krb5 in the berval2tl_data() function in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c. The function performs an unsigned subtraction (bv_len - 2) without a prior bounds check. When bv_len is 0 or 1, the subtraction wraps to a large value which is then truncated to uint16_t, yielding 0xFFFE (65534) or 0xFFFF (65535). The subsequent malloc succeeds and memcpy reads up to 65534 bytes from a 0-1 byte buffer, resulting in a heap out-of-bounds read. The attack vector involves a malicious or compromised LDAP KDB backend returning a krbExtraData attribute with bv_len \u003c 2, triggering the underflow when the KDC or kadmind reads principal data."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-11850",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-11850\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libgssapi-krb5-2\nVersion: 1.22.1-2.1\nFix Version: 1.22.1-3\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-11850](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-11850)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-11850**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | libgssapi-krb5-2  | 1.22.1-2.1  | 1.22.1-3  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-11850](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-11850)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libgssapi-krb5-2@1.22.1-2.1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=krb5"
                ],
                "security-severity": "5.0"
              }
            },
            {
